<HEADLINE> Arafat, Algerian President Hold Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALGIERS, September 28 (Xinhua) -- Algerian President Liamine
Zeroual today held talks with visiting Palestinian National
Authority (PNA) Chairman Yasser Arafat on the stalled Middle East
peace process.
</P>
<P>
Arafat, who flew to Algeria earlier today, discussed with
Zeroual on the latest developments in the peace process and its
prospects, and Israel's intransigent policies, according to
informed officials.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders agreed to strengthen bilateral ties and
increase cooperation on regional issues. But details of the
meeting were not available.
</P>
<P>
Arafat's visit to Algeria is believed to be part of an effort
to rally support of African countries in the face of Israel's
provocative and hardline policy.
</P>
<P>
Arafat was to continue his trip to Tunisia after his meetings
here. 
</P>
</TEXT>
