<HEADLINE> Van Roost Claims Indonesian Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YAKARTA, September 28 (Xinhua) -- Top seed Dominique Van Roost
of Belgium won her second Tour title Sunday after beating unseeded
Czech Lenka Nemeckova 6-1, 6-3 in the final of the Wismilak
International in Surabaya.
</P>
<P>
Van Roost overcame early nerves and the loss of her opening
service game to love to win eight straight games and set up an
ultimately effortless triumph over her 106th-ranked opponent,
reports reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
Van Roost sent down a string of meaty returns to the back court
as she forced Nemeckova onto the defensive throughout in what was
the Czech girl's first Tour final.
</P>
<P>
Rank outsider Nemeckova held her serve in the second set to
lead 1-0 but there followed five straight breaks before Van Roost
held for 5-3. The Belgian then completed the victory with a
crushing forehand return.  
</P>
</TEXT>
