<HEADLINE> China, Russia to Regulate Border Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, September 29 (Xinhua) -- China and Russia have agreed
to tighten crackdowns on illegal trade activities along the border
of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Officials from the State Administration for Commerce and
Industry of China and their Russian counterparts reached an
agreement at a meeting today that measures should be taken to
solve the problems of unfair competition and trade monoploy.
</P>
<P>
The move is to ensure a healthy economic and trade relationship
between China and Russia, officials said.
</P>
<P>
The two sides announced that a long-term cooperative program
based on governmental agreements will be conducted to fight unfair
competition and monopoly, and protect consumers' rights. Joint
actions will be taken to target economic fraud, they said.
</P>
<P>
They also vowed to maintain timely information exchange and
tighten law enforcement to honor trade contracts and guarantee
quality of goods.
</P>
<P>
China and Russia share a 4,300-kilometer border, on which the
two sides have opened dozens of trade posts. Border trade has
become an important component of the bilateral economy and trade.
</P>
