<HEADLINE> Chile Fire Kills 31 Children </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, September 29 (Xinhua) -- At least 31 children were
killed and dozens of others injured early today when a fire swept
through a home for mentally retarded children in northern Chile,
police sources said.
</P>
<P>
Most of those killed were infants.
</P>
<P>
When the fire broke out, more than 200 children were sleeping
in the building, which is located about 40 kilometers north of the
country's capital.
</P>
<P>
Police said the fire may have been triggered by a short-circuit
in the building.
</P>
<P>
Chilean Minister of the Interior Carlos Figueroa Serrano
visited the mental institution later today and urged a deeper
investigation into the tragedy. 
