<HEADLINE> At Least 9 Dead in Multiple-Truck Collision in France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, September 29 (Xinhua) -- At least nine people were
killed and dozens injured in a multiple-truck collision that
occurred this morning on a national highway in the Eure Province,
west of Paris, Agence France-Presse (AFP) reported.
</P>
<P>
The provincial police commander Dominique Lapprand did not rule
out the possibility that the number of casualties could continue
to rise.
</P>
<P>
Several trucks caught fire after crashing into each other in
four separate collisions at 10:00 a.m. (09:00 GMT).
</P>
<P>
Some of the trucks carried the remains of "dangerous
substances," which caused them to catch fire, said authorities.
</P>
<P>
The negligence of one truck driver reportedly led to the
accident, the police said.
</P>
<P>
Some 160 firemen, 120 policemen and many ambulances and rescue
vehicles rushed to the scene of the accident, said the AFP.
</P>
