<HEADLINE> Legend, Hitachi to Jointly Develop New Desk Computers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 29 (Xinhua) -- Legend Group, China's leading
computer maker, and Hitachi Ltd of Japan announced here today they
will form a strategic cooperative alliance, conduct full-dimension
technical cooperation and jointly develop new-concept desk
computers.
</P>
<P>
The project plays up the highly complementary strong points of
the Chinese and Japanese manufacturers engaged in information
technology.
</P>
<P>
As for their advantages, Hitachi has commanded the technology
of key components and has mastered the latest technological
information and resources, as well as advanced management
expertise concerning technological development.
</P>
<P>
Legend designs complete sets of computers, and has
highly-competent technical personnel and uses the world's
most-sophisticated technology in its production.
</P>
<P>
According to an agreement signed between them, Legend will be
fully responsible for making the new products to be sold at home
and abroad.
</P>
<P>
Experts say the new-concept computers will be more space- and
energy-efficient than the traditional models and will produce less
harmful radiation.
</P>
<P>
Yang Yuanqing, deputy president of Legend Group, disclosed that
the new generation of the computers jointly developed by both
sides will be put into the market in small batches by the end of
the year, and will show marked improvement in both function and
appearance.
</P>
<P>
It is expected that Legend will produce 400,000 computers this
year. The Chinese computer maker was recently named one of the top
ten sellers in the Asian-Pacific region in a survey on the
region's PC market conducted by Dataquest, a well-known market
surveyor.
</P>
<P>
Last year, Legend scored 7.7 billion yuan in computer sales,
ranking first in China.
</P>
<P>
Founded in 1984, Legend Group has grown into a multi-functional
conglomerate with 26 domestic branches and sub-branches, 21
overseas firms, and total assets of 2.8 billion yuan. Last year,
it ranked second among China's 100 top electronics enterprises and
was listed by the Ministry of Electronics Industry as one of the six
major conglomerates that will receive hefty state support.
</P>
<P>
Hitachi is a world-renowned electrical machinery manufacturer,
chalking up 68.7 billion U.S. dollars in total sales in 1996 and
ranking fifth among the world's computer-manufacturing companies.
</P>
<P>
The establishment of long-term strategic cooperation ties
between Legend and the world's computer giants such as Microsoft,
Intel and Hitachi, shows that the Chinese computer maker is no
longer focused solely on the domestic market. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
