<HEADLINE> World Leaders Congratulate China on National Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 29 (Xinhua) -- Leaders of the Democratic
People's Republic of Korea (DPRK), Georgia, Germany and other
countries have sent messages of congratulations to President
Jiang Zemin on China's 48th National Day on October 1.
</P>
<P>
In his message, Kim Jong Il, chairman of the National Defense
Commission of DPRK and the Supreme Commander of the Korean People's
Army, described the founding of the People's Republic of China as
an epoch-making event for Chinese people.
</P>
<P>
It was after the founding of the People's Republic of China
that the Chinese people became the real masters of their own
country and found a new way to create a totally different kind of
life from the old society, Kim said.
</P>
<P>
Under the leadership of the Communist Party of China (CPC)
during the past 48 years, the self-reliant Chinese people
carried forward the practice of plain living and hard struggle,
surmounted difficulties, put an end to the history of
impoverishment and backwardness and established a new socialist
China, Kim said.
</P>
<P>
He added that with the efforts of the CPC and the Chinese
government, China has played a more important role in the
international community.
</P>
<P>
Kim spoke warmly of the achievements the Chinese people --
under the leadership of the CPC headed by Jiang -- have made in
fulfilling the mission of establishing a modern socialist country
with Chinese characteristics and realizing the unification of the
motherland.
</P>
<P>
As for the traditional friendship between DPRK and China, Kim
said it is the persistent policy for both parties and countries to
strengthen and develop such a friendly relationship.
</P>
<P>
In another message of congratulations, Georgian President
Eduard Shevardnadze praised China's reform policy and the great
achievements the Chinese people have made under the policy.
</P>
<P>
He said China has set an example for those countries which are
seeking their own positions in modern society.
</P>
<P>
Shevardnadze also mentioned Hong Kong's return to the
motherland on July 1, which, the president said, proved again that
the choice made by the Chinese leadership was correct.
</P>
<P>
German President Roman Herzog said in his message that China's
rapid development in the past 20 years has attracted worldwide
attention.
</P>
<P>
As for China's resumption of the exercise of sovereignty over
Hong Kong, Herzog said it was a historic event for all Chinese
people.
</P>
<P>
He added that he believed Hong Kong, after returning to its
motherland, would maintain its prosperity and development and make
greater contributions to its motherland's modernization drive.
</P>
<P>
Other leaders who also sent messages of congratulations to
Jiang on China's National Day include the following:
</P>
<P>
President of the Republic of Kyrgyzstan Askar Akayevich Akayev;
</P>
<P>
President of Azerbaijan Geidar Aliyev;
</P>
<P>
President of the Republic of Equatorial Guinea Teodoro Obiang
Nguema Mbasogo;
</P>
<P>
President of Greece Costis Stephanopoulos;
</P>
<P>
President of the Republic of Kenya Daniel Arap Moi;
</P>
<P>
President of the Republic of Malta Ugo Mifsud Bonnici;
</P>
<P>
Chairman of Myanma's State Law and Order Restoration Council
Than Shwe;
</P>
<P>
Queen of the Kingdom of the Netherlands Beatrix Wilhelmina
Armgard;
</P>
<P>
President of the Islamic Republic of Pakistan Farooq Leghari;
</P>
<P>
President of Turkmenistan Saparmurad Atayevich Niyazov;
</P>
<P>
Director-General of the Food and Agricultural Organization of
the United Nations Jacques Diouf.
</P>
<P>
Leaders who sent a message of congratulations to Premier Li
Peng on China's National Day included:
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister of Barbados Owen Arthur;
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister of Myanma Than Shwe;
</P>
