<HEADLINE> State Council Hosts National Day Reception for Overseas Chinese (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 28 (Xinhua) -- More than 1,100 people,
including compatriots from the Hong Kong Special Administrative
Region (SAR), Macao and Taiwan and overseas Chinese and Chinese
nationals residing overseas, joined a grand reception here this
evening to mark the 48th founding anniversary of the People's
Republic of China.
</P>
<P>
Qian Qichen, a member of the Political Bureau of the Communist
Party of China (CPC)'s Central Committee and vice-premier,
delivered a speech at the reception, jointly hosted by the Office
of Overseas Chinese Affairs, Hong Kong and Macao Affairs Office
and Taiwan Affairs Office under the State Council.
</P>
<P>
On behalf of the Chinese government and people, Qian extended
sincere appreciation to all Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan
compatriots and overseas Chinese for their persistent concern,
support and assistance to China's reform, opening-up and
modernization drive.
</P>
<P>
He said that over the past 48 years, especially in the past two
decades of reforms and opening-up, tremendous changes have taken
place in China.
</P>
<P>
"History has proved that building socialism with Chinese
characteristics is the only road that will lead us to national
prosperity and happiness for everyone," he said.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the 15th CPC National Congress, which was
convened here from September 12 to 18, has made comprehensive
plans for the cross-century development of China's reform,
opening-up and modernization drive, and will surely have a
significant impact on China's future.
</P>
</TEXT>
