<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 14:30 GMT, September 29 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING -- Japanese ambassador to China Yoshiyasu Sato hosted a
reception here today to mark the 25th anniversary of the
normalization of diplomatic ties between China and Japan.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the reception, Ambassador Sato said that on this
special occasion, it is very significant to review the history
between the two countries and look to the future to promote the
growth of bilateral relations. (China-Japan-Ambassador)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ISLAMABAD -- Pakistan today expressed "serious concern" on the
reports regarding the commencement of regular production of
Prithvi Missiles by India.
</P>
<P>
The production of Prithvi, which is capable of carrying nuclear
warheads, represents a qualitative change in the fragile security
situation of the region, a Pakistani spokesman
said. (Pakistan-India-Missile)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
NEW DELHI -- At least 15 people were killed and 27 others
injured when an overcrowded bus fell into a ditch in India's West
Bengal state on Sunday, Press Trust of India said today.
</P>
<P>
The ill-fated bus rammed into a lamp post and overturned before
it fell into the ditch. (India-Traffic Accident)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TOKYO -- Japanese Prime Minister Ryutaro Hashimoto today vowed
to expand cooperative relations with China and other neighboring
countries.
</P>
<P>
Hashimoto made the pledge in a major policy speech to the 141st
extraordinary session of the Japanese Diet (parliament) which
opened here today.
</P>
<P>
Hailing the 25th anniversary of normalization of Sino-Japanese
diplomatic ties, Hashimoto expressed hopes for deepening dialogue
at various levels and strengthening trust between the two
countries. (Japan-Diet-Hashimoto)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
NEW DELHI -- An indigenously built Indian rocket today blasted
off from a launching center in India's Andhra Pradesh, Press Trust
of India said.
</P>
<P>
The Polar Satellite Launch Vehicle (PSLV) will place a
1,200-kilogram remote sensing satellite into an 817-kilometer
polar sun-synchronous orbit. (India-Missile-Launch)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JAKARTA -- At least 17 people were killed and 331 others
injured in the tectonic earthquake measuring 6.4 on the Richter
scale which jolted Indonesia's south Sulawesi province Sunday,
Antara news agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The quake, which started at 9:38 a.m. local time and lasted for
several minutes, hit a number of districts such as Pinrang,
Pare-Pare, Sidrap and Polewali as well as Ujungpandang, capital of
the province. (Indonesia-Quake-Toll) 
</P>
