<HEADLINE> HK Land Fund Trust Ends Historical Mission </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 29 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region Government (HKSARG) Land Fund Trust, which
was set up at the early stage of the transition period to manage
HKSARG's share of land premium income, has completed its
historical mission and will dissolve tomorrow.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a farewell reception here today, Chen Rongchun, one
of the Land Fund's three trustees, announced, the Land Fund Trust
will submit the Final Accounts to Chief Executive Tung Chee Hwa
tomorrow and dissolve on the same day.
</P>
<P>
When the Land Fund was established in August 1986, its net
assets were only 772 million HK dollars (99 million U.S. dollars),
Chen said.
</P>
<P>
Thanks to prudent management and effective operation over the
past 11 years, the Land Fund, through to the date of handover, has
increased its net assets to 170.7 billion HK dollars (21.9 billion
U.S. dollars), of which 123.6 billion HK dollars (15.8 billion
U.S. dollars) represent land premium income and 47.1 billion HK
dollars (6.0 billion U.S. dollars) accumulated investment surplus,
he noted.
</P>
<P>
Adding the share of land premium income for the three-month
period from April 1 to June 30 of 26.4 billion HK dollars (3.4
billion U.S. dollars), which was received by the Land Fund on
August 29, the trustees have handed over the HKSARG net assets
valued at 197.1 billion HK dollars (25.3 billion U.S. dollars),
Chen said.
</P>
<P>
"This performance has fully proved that the original decision
of establishing the Land Fund was timely and correct and the
anticipated goal of safety, preservation and appreciation of the
Fund has been realized and remarkable wealth has been created for
the HKSARG as well as over six million people of Hong Kong," Chen
commented.
</P>
<P>
On July 1, the establishment day of the HKSARG, China's Vice
Premier Qian Qichen, on behalf of the Central Government, had
formally handed over the Land Fund to the chief executive.
</P>
<P>
The Land Fund is now being managed as part of HKSARG's fiscal
reserves by the Hong Kong Monetary Authority under the direction
of the financial secretary, Donald Tsang.
</P>
<P>
Chen said, the Land Fund "lays a solid foundation for the
finances of the HKSARG and at the same time contributes to
maintaining the status of Hong Kong as an international financial
center, stabilizing the exchange rate of Hong Kong dollar and
facilitating the economic and social development of the HKSAR."
</P>
<P>
Also addressing the reception were Tung Chee Hwa and Jiang
Enzhu, the director of Xinhua News Agency Hong Kong Branch.
</P>
<P>
Tung, on behalf of the HKSARG and people of Hong Kong, thanked
the three trustees appointed by the Central Government for
creating remarkable wealth for Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
He acclaimed that the Fund has played a major and stabilizing
role in the early days of the HKSARG, adding its establishment
demonstrated both the care for the HKSARG and the vision of the
Central Government.
</P>
<P>
He also pointed to the fact that the Fund has weathered one
after another global financial crisis over the past years to
achieve an average annual rate of return of 9.09 percent, which is
about one percentage point higher than the annual inflation rate.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
