<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK External Trade Up in August </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 29 (Xinhua) -- The value of Hong Kong's
total exports in August rose 3.7 percent over the same month last
year to 129.5 billion HK dollars (16.60 billion U.S. dollars),
while the value of imports increased 5.8 percent to 139.8 billion
HK dollars (17.92 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Official statistics released today show that a visible trade
deficit of 10.3 billion HK dollars (1.32 billion U.S. dollars),
equivalent to 7.4 percent of the value of imports, was recorded.
</P>
<P>
This was larger than the corresponding deficit of 7.2 billion
HK dollars (0.92 billion U.S. dollars), equivalent to 5.5 percent
of the value of imports, in August 1996.
</P>
<P>
For the first eight months of 1997 as a whole, the value of
total exports increased by 3.3 percent over the same period last
year, while the value of imports showed an increase of 5.4
percent.
</P>
<P>
For the first eight months combined, a visible trade deficit of
121.1 billion HK dollars (15.53 billion U.S. dollars), equivalent
to 11 percent of the value of imports, was recorded. This was
larger than the deficit of 97.6 billion HK dollars (12.51 billion
U.S. dollars), equivalent to 9.7 percent of the value of imports,
recorded in the same period in 1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
