<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-Premier Meets Nepalese Visitors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 29 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Jiang
Chunyun met today with a delegation of Nepal, led by Pradeep
Shrestha, first vice-president of the Federation of the Nepalese
Chambers of Commerce and Industry.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said since the first China-Nepal Non-Governmental
Cooperation Forum Meeting last year, there has been wide
cooperation between industrial and commercial sectors of the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
The second meeting of its kind has ended successfully with
several agreements of cooperation, showing that the
non-governmental cooperation between the two nations has entered a
substantial phase, he noted.
</P>
<P>
The Vice-Premier noted that China and Nepal, as two developing
nations, are economically complementary. He hoped industrial and
commercial circles of the two countries could work out more
projects with less investment and quick results to benefit the
peoples, and enhance a steady development of bilateral trade and
economic cooperation.
</P>
<P>
He briefed the visitors on the 15th National Congress of the
Communist Party of China (CPC).
</P>
<P>
Shrestha gave Jiang a brief introduction on the growth of
non-governmental exchanges between the Nepal and China and hoped
to further expand the exchanges.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed his congratulations on Hong Kong's smooth
return to the motherland and the successful conclusion of the
CPC's 15th National Congress. 
</P>
</TEXT>
