<HEADLINE> Suspected Drug Traffickers Arrested in S. Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, September 29 (Xinhua) -- Two passengers were
arrested separately in South Africa's Cape Town and Johannesburg
international airports on Friday after they were found to have
swallowed 137 condoms filled with cocaine, police said today.
</P>
<P>
A man from South America was detained at Cape Town
International Airport after an X-ray check found that there were
70 condoms in his stomach filled with cocaine, the South African
Press Association (SAPA) quoted a Cape Town police spokeswoman as
saying.
</P>
<P>
The cocaine weighed one kilogram and had a street value of
350,000 Rand (about 74,000 U.S. Dollars).
</P>
<P>
The suspect was given laxatives and expunged the condoms
during the next 24 hours.
</P>
<P>
A second man was arrested at Johannesburg International
Airport after he was found to have swallowed 67 condoms filled
with cocaine with a street value of 283,500 Rand (60,300
Dollars), SAPA quoted another local police spokeswoman as saying.
</P>
<P>
Johannesburg-based detectives detained the man after they
received information from their Cape Town colleagues that a
possible drug courier was identified on a domestic flight bound
for Johannesburg.
</P>
<P>
The cocaine he swallowed weighed 945 grams.
</P>
<P>
Last month, a 24-year-old Johannesburg woman was arrested at
Cape Town International Airport in possession of a kilogram of
cocaine. 
</P>
</TEXT>
