<HEADLINE> ADB Approves Loan for China's Railway Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 29 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank
(ADB) today approved a 200 million U.S. dollars loan to help China
fund a railway project in its resource-rich northwestern province
of Shanxi.
</P>
<P>
A new 368-kilometer railway line linking the cities of Shenmu
and Yanan will open up abundant resources of low sulfur coal in
mineral-rich but land-locked Shanxi province, the Manila-based
financial body said.
</P>
<P>
The project will create 370,000 new jobs by 2005 and
drastically reduce poverty from 22 percent to 5 percent in a
region where the lack of transport links has been a major
constraint to development, the bank said.
</P>
<P>
The ADB will also provide a technical assistance grant of
400,000 dollars to help the local railway companies in Shanxi
province develop financially viable commercial operations.
</P>
<P>
The Shanxi Xiyan Railway Company will be the executing agency
for the project, which is due for completion in December 2002.
</P>
<P>
The ADB loan, drawn from its ordinary capital resources, will
have an interest rate determined in accordance with the bank's
pool-based variable lending rate system for U.S. dollars.
</P>
</TEXT>
