<HEADLINE> Bebeto Signs Again With Deportivo Coruna </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, September 29 (Xinhua) -- Brazilian international
striker Bebeto has signed a two-year contract with Deportivo
Coruna of Spain, said the club president Augusto Cesar Lendoiro
Monday.
</P>
<P>
Lendoiro said in a news conference in La Coruna, Spain that he
had received a fax from Brazilian club Vitoria which confirmed the
transfer.
</P>
<P>
No finantial details were released.
</P>
<P>
33-year-old Bebeto played for Deportivo in 1992-1996 before
moving to Flamengo of Brazil.
</P>
<P>
He joined Vitoria in January after initially turning down
Deportivo's offers.
</P>
<P>
However, the Brazilian star refused to return to Vitoria four
weeks ago when he was injured in a match, and received a
punishment of suspendence of wages for his indiscipline. 
</P>
</TEXT>
