<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pakistan Concerned over Indian Missile Production </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, September 29 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan today expressed
"serious concern" on the reports regarding the commencement of
regular production of Prithvi Missiles by India.
</P>
<P>
"India's decision is bound to escalate tension and add to the
deterioration of the security climate in the area," a Foreign
Office spokesman said here today, adding South Asia was among the
few remaining "flash points" in the post-cold war world.
</P>
<P>
The production of Prithvi, which is capable of carrying nuclear
warheads, represents a qualitative change in the fragile security
situation of the region, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
"It was regrettable that New Delhi has responded by induction
of sophisticated missile systems while Pakistan was pushing for
confidence building measures including a zero missile regime in
South Asia, and has offered a "Non-Aggression Pact" to India," he
said.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said the timing of the announcement of these
militarization programs coinciding with the announcement of
India's candidature for a permanent seat of the U.N. Security
Council is "curious".
</P>
<P>
"Adherence to the Charter of the United Nations and respect for
Security Council Resolutions rather than military might should be
the criteria in this campaign," he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
