<HEADLINE> Japanese Ambassador Hosts Reception Honoring Sino-Japanese Relations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 29 (Xinhua) -- Japanese ambassador to China
Yoshiyasu Sato hosted a reception here today to mark the 25th
anniversary of the normalization of diplomatic ties between China
and Japan.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the reception, Ambassador Sato said that on this
special occasion, it is very significant to review the history
between the two countries and look to the future to promote the
growth of bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
Chinese State Councillor Li Tieying reviewed the 25 years of
development of bilateral ties, and expressed his thanks and
gratitude to those who dedicated themselves to the cause of
rebuilding and developing Sino-Japanese friendly relations.
</P>
<P>
He hoped that the two sides could abide by the Sino-Japanese
Joint Statement and the Sino-Japanese Treaty of Peace and
Friendship, spare no effort to strengthen bilateral
good-neighborly friendship oriented to the future, and pass it on
from generation to generation.
</P>
<P>
Former Japanese Prime Minister Noboru Takeshita and
personalities of the relevant departments from the two countries
also attended the reception. 
</P>
</TEXT>
