<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Deposits, Loans, Advances Fall Slightly in August </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 29 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's total deposits,
loans and advances fell slightly during August 1997, according to
statistics published today by the Hong Kong Monetary Authority
(HKMA).
</P>
<P>
Total deposits declined by 0.8 percent in the month, reversing
a 0.5 percent rise in July. The fall was primarily attributable to
a 1.4 percent drop in HK dollar deposits, which more than offset
an increase of 0.2 percent in foreign currency deposits.
</P>
<P>
The HKMA release said the fall in HK dollar deposits was
across-the-board, partly reflecting the less buoyant asset
markets.
</P>
<P>
In line with the fall in deposits, total loans and advances
declined by 0.4 percent in August, which dropped by 0.6 percent in
July. 
</P>
</TEXT>
