<HEADLINE> Japan, China Celebrate Normalization of Diplomatic Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, September 29 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Embassy in Japan
today hosted a grand reception to celebrate the 25th anniversary
of the normalization of Sino-Japanese diplomatic ties.
</P>
<P>
During the reception, Japanese Prime Minister Ryutaro Hashimoto
said that Japan and China will conduct dialogues in security and
other fields to establish a more friendly relationship that will
contribute to development in the Asia-Pacific region and the world.
</P>
<P>
He said bilateral ties between Japan and China would also
improve because of the increasing number of visits by leaders of
both countries.
</P>
<P>
More than 1,200 guests from Japan's various circles, overseas
Chinese community and foreign diplomats attended the reception.
</P>
<P>
Foreign Minister Keizo Obuchi, Chief Cabinet Secretary Kanezo
Muraoka, Finance Minister Hiroshi Mitsuzuka, former Prime
Ministers Yasuhiro Nakasone and Tomiichi Murayama and other
government officials were also present at the occasion.
</P>
<P>
The Sino-Japanese relations in various fields have been
developing rapidly since the two countries normalized their
diplomatic relations in 1972 and concluded a peace and friendship
treaty in 1978. 
</P>
