<HEADLINE> China, Nepal Seek for More Economic Cooperation Chances </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 29 (Xinhua) -- The second Chinese-Nepalese
non-governmental cooperation forum closed here today after signing
a number of joint contracts.
</P>
<P>
During the two-day meeting, personnel from the industrial and
commercial circles of the two countries discussed trade issues,
such as how to increase trade volumes of the two sides, how to
eliminate obstacles to successful trade, how to reduce the trade
deficit, how to increase Chinese investment in Nepal, and
determining the feasibility of setting up joint ventures in the
two countries.
</P>
<P>
Entrepreneurs of the two sides negotiated on terms of
cooperation in fields of hydro-electric power, electronics, light
industry, handicrafts, textiles, and tourism.
</P>
<P>
Nanjing Xike Group of east China's Jiangsu province signed a
contract to supply Nepal with 10,000 mini-generators to be
manufactured in Nepal.
</P>
<P>
Chen Wen, president of the Xike group, said that the economic
similarities shared by China and Nepal has enabled Chinese private
businesses to seek business opportunities in South Asia.
</P>
<P>
Chen held that Chinese private businesses would succeed in
economic cooperation projects in the region.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese-Nepalese economic cooperation forum, initiated by
the governments of China and Nepal in 1996, was held for the first
time in Kathmandu, Nepal last October. 
</P>
</TEXT>
