<HEADLINE> Guangxi to Open Channels to Lure Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, September 29 (Xinhua) -- The Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous
Region in south China is opening more channels to raise money
for construction of key projects.
</P>
<P>
Insufficient investment in fixed assets has long been
considered a bottleneck for the local economic development. The
growth rate of fixed assets investment was 3.2 percent lower than
the country's average in the first half of this year.
</P>
<P>
The region will turn to both domestic and overseas investors to
attract cash inflow, according to local officials, and will list
more local large and medium-sized enterprises on the stock market,
and establish capital funds.
</P>
<P>
Plans have also been made to transfer the operating rights of
some highways and bridges to overseas investors, and regional
officials are applying for international commercial loans.
</P>
<P>
Guangxi will also increase cooperation with Hong Kong and
neighboring Guangdong Province to boost its economy.  
</P>
