<HEADLINE> Croatia Attracts More Foreign Tourists This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZAGREB, September 29 (Xinhua) -- As the warfare calms down,
Croatia have attracted 49 percent more foreign tourists,
registering 3.3 million in the first eight months of this year,
according to the Croatian Bureau of Statistics.
</P>
<P>
Domestic tourists made up for one million, or ten percent more
than a year ago.
</P>
<P>
According to the Tourism Ministry, a total of 1.56 million
tourist arrivals have been registered in this August alone.
</P>
<P>
Germans were the most numerous to spend their holidays in
the country throughout the first eight months of 1997, with 4.5
million overnight stays, followed by the Czech, with 3.7 million
overnight stays, the Slovenes, with 3.5 million, the Italians with
three million, and the Austrians with 2.4 million overnight stays.
</P>
<P>
The ministry expected that tourist trade will register a
40-percent increase this year. 
</P>
