<HEADLINE> Mozambique Preparing for Possible Drought </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, September 29 (Xinhua) -- The Mozambican government is
preparing itself for a possible drought brought about by the El
Nino phenomenon, the Noticias paper said today, quoted a senior
official.
</P>
<P>
Experts predict that El Nino will reduce the rainfalls in
central and southern Mozambique from November till next March,
causing drought, Silvano Langa, Director of the Department for
Prevention and Combat of Natural Calamities.
</P>
<P>
Plans have been worked out for the needs of food and water in
drought-hit areas, for the provision of drought resistant crops
in the next season and replaceable pastures, he said.
</P>
<P>
A delegation of the World Food Program (WFP) is now touring
the country to make investigation and decide on the effects of El
Nino, the affected areas and people.
</P>
<P>
Another WFP mission will come here in early October to
estimate the capability of Mozambique's logistics, Langa said.
</P>
</TEXT>
