<HEADLINE> NPC Chairman Meets Canadian University President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 29 (Xinhua) -- Qiao Shi, chairman of the
Chinese National People's Congress (NPC) Standing Committee, met
with Donald Wells, president of University of Regina of Canada,
and Mrs. Wells in the Great Hall of the People here today.
</P>
<P>
Qiao welcomed Wells and thanked him for contributing to the
betterment of Sino-Canadian cultural and educational exchanges.
</P>
<P>
Qiao happily recalled his 1994 visit to the Canadian university
which offered him an honorary doctoral degree, saying this was not
only an honor for him, but also a symbol of China-Canada
friendship.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the maintaining of a long-term and in-depth
exchange of contacts between the two countries is conducive to the
promotion of bilateral educational, scientific and technological
development, and beneficial to the advancement of bilateral
friendly relations oriented towards the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
The NPC and the Chinese government are taking a positive
attitude to this end, he added.
</P>
<P>
He stated that China is enjoying rapid growth and the Chinese
people are full of confidence in the future. He expressed the hope
to further tighten bilateral cooperation and exchanges in fields
of education, science and technology.
</P>
<P>
Wan Xueyuan, director of China's State Bureau of Foreign
Experts, was present at today's meeting.
</P>
<P>
Wells, as a guest of the bureau, had also visited a number of
colleges and universities in the provinces of Shandong, Shaanxi,
Hubei and Jilin.  
</P>
