<DOCNO> XIE19970929.0084 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pakistan Strives to Increase Agri-production </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, September 29 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan Federal Government
has prepared a comprehensive plan to increase the agricultural
production with an aim to completely end its dependence on import
of food items, officials said.
</P>
<P>
The 9th Five-Year Development Plan beginning from next year
envisaged 3.83 percent annual increase in wheat production, 3.22
percent in rice production and 7.86 percent in cotton production,
the officials said.
</P>
<P>
The increase in agri-production will not be achieved through
the significant increase in the area under cultivation, but by
changing the cropping pattern and getting the higher per acre
yield through the use of latest agri-technology, they said.
</P>
<P>
The government was keen to achieve food autarky in the country,
because a sizable portion of national income is being spent on the
import of food items, they said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
