<HEADLINE> China Gets "Green Buses" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, September 29 (Xinhua) -- The first ten buses fueled
with liquefied natural gas are now driving down the streets of
Haikou, capital of China's southernmost Hainan Province.
</P>
<P>
This makes Haikou the third Chinese city after Guangzhou and
Shenzhen to use natural gas-driven vehicles.
</P>
<P>
The buses burning natural gas are considered safe and
environmentally-friendly, and will help to curb the increasing air
pollution in cities caused by excessive auto emissions.
</P>
<P>
The "green buses" emit 70 percent less pollutant fumes,
according to automobile experts.
</P>
<P>
Haikou will invest a total of 30 million yuan to install a
natural-gas fuel burning system to 5,400 buses and cars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
