<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Singapore PM Awarded S$20,000 in Defamation Case </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, September 29 (Xinhua) -- The High Court of Singapore
awarded Prime Minister Goh Chok Tong 20,000 Singapore dollars, or
13,160 U.S. dollars at current exchange rate, in damages in his
defamation suit against opposition Workers' Party leader J.B.
Jeyaretnam, Singapore television reported today.
</P>
<P>
The case arose out of Jeyaretnam's words at an election rally
on the eve of the polling day early this year.
</P>
<P>
The plaintiff's case was that Jeyaretnam had defamed the Prime
Minister for criminal activity by saying that the then Workers'
Party candidate Tang Liang Hong had placed before Jeyaretnam
police reports against "Mr. Goh Chok Tong and his people".
</P>
<P>
In his 142-page judgment, Justice S. Rajendran said because of
the high standing of the Prime Minister, Mr. Goh was awarded
10,000 Singapore dollars in general damages.
</P>
<P>
An ordinary man, the Judge said, on hearing the words, could
have believed the Prime Minister might be investigated for an
offense.
</P>
<P>
But he added that the level of defamation was not as high as
claimed by Mr. Goh, which meant the words implied that Mr. Goh had
committed the alleged criminal offenses, the television report
said.
</P>
<P>
It said that another 10,000 Singapore dollars was awarded to
Mr. Goh as "aggravated damages". Justice Rajendran said that this
was because Jeyaretnam acted with reckless disregard to the
consequences of his actions, the report said.
</P>
<P>
He also took into account Jeyaretnam's conduct of his defense
during the trial, where, the report said, his lawyer tried to put
government policy on the stand, with little or nothing to back up
the accusations.
</P>
<P>
The Prime Minister was also awarded 60 percent of the court
costs, which means that he can claim from Jeyaretnam costs of the
five-day trial last month, the report said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
