industrials index down 10.2 points to 4578.3 and the all resources
up 7.4 points to 1353.6.
</P>
<P>
Traders said today's comments by the Reserve Bank of Australia
Governor Ian Macfarlane about inflation suggested a tight rein
would be kept on the economy, dampening anticipation of a
near-term rate cut.
</P>
<P>
National Australia Bank was the biggest drifter on the market
today, down 61 cents to 21.75 Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
