<HEADLINE> Traffic Accident Kills 15 in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 29 (Xinhua) -- At least 15 people were
killed and 27 others injured when an overcrowded bus fell into a
ditch in India's West Bengal state on Sunday, Press Trust of India
said today.
</P>
<P>
The ill-fated bus rammed into a lamp post and overturned before
it fell into the ditch.
</P>
<P>
All the injured were stated to be in serious condition.
</P>
<P>
Also on Sunday, 16 people were feared killed and 24 injured
when a bus carrying 42 passengers fell into a river in Uttar
Pradesh.
</P>
<P>
Two passengers swam to safety, 16 were missing and feared dead
and the rest were injured, police said.  
