<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Philippines to Phase Out Leaded Gasoline </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 29 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Fidel
Ramos today approved the phase-out of leaded gasoline by the end
of the century as one of the measures to solve the worsening air
pollution in the country.
</P>
<P>
Under a newly-signed executive order by Ramos, leaded gasoline
will be phased out in Metro Manila not later than January 1, 2000
and other parts of the country by January 1, 2001.
</P>
<P>
Ramos described the signing of the order as "very timely" in
view of the fact that the country is now experiencing two major
environmental disasters: the El Nino phenomenon and the haze
brought by forest fire in Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
Wide use of leaded gasoline by some kinds of vehicles is
considered one of the main factors that cause the severe air
pollution problem in the Philippines.  
</P>
</TEXT>
