<HEADLINE> Sabah Frames Maritime Industry Development Strategy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, September 29 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia's Sabah state
today launched its Maritime Strategic Development Framework as an
initial step towards developing the sector in the state.
</P>
<P>
The framework, launched today by the state Chief Minister Yong
Teck Lee in the state's capital Kota Kinabalu, spells out several
objectives including developing infrastructure and support
services, improving sea links, developing the shipbuilding
industry, and continued use of marine resources.
</P>
<P>
Under the framework, the state Communication and Works Ministry
would be in charge of maritime matters in the state, according to
a report by the Malaysian national news agency Bernama from Kota
Kinabalu.
</P>
<P>
The documents on the development of the maritime sector are
important to Sabah in its efforts to position itself as a regional
center for the maritime industry, especially in the East ASEAN
Growth Area (EAGA) comprising Brunei, Indonesia, Malaysia and the
Philippines, Yong was quoted by Bernama as saying.
</P>
<P>
Such a framework would provide a guide on the direction of the
industry in the state now and in future, where previously there
was no special reference center for the maritime sector, the chief
minister said.
</P>
<P>
Yong also said that Sabah would organize the Sabah
International Maritime Exhibition next September as part of its
efforts to promote the maritime industry in the state.  
</P>
</TEXT>
