<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Closes Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, September 29 (Xinhua) -- The travel allowance brawl,
which has engulfed the Australian federal government over the past
week, today took its toll on the Australian dollar, which ended
weaker against the US dollar.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar closed half a US cent lower at 71.86 US
cents, down from 72.36 US cents locally late Friday.
</P>
<P>
Traders said offshore participants backed away from the
domestic unit, reflecting their concern over the fact that the
mistaken travel allowance claim scandal, which last week saw three
government ministers and two senior advisors to Prime Minister
John Howard resign, could further destabilize the government.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar was at 87.16 yen, from 87.60, and at
1.2616 marks, from 1.7523.  
</P>
