<HEADLINE> Kabila Arrives in Lusaka on First Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, September 29 (Xinhua) -- Laurent-Desire Kabila,
President of the Democratic Republic of Congo, arrived here this
morning for his first official visit to Zambia since he took
power last may in former Zaire.
</P>
<P>
On his arrival at the Lusaka international airport, Kabila,
accompanied by a high powered delegation, received a warm welcome
by his Zambian counterpart President Federick Chiluba and dozens
of Zambian senior officials.
</P>
<P>
At the invitation of Chiluba, Kabila will pay a three-day
official visit to his southeastern neighbor of Zambia.
</P>
<P>
During his stay, he is scheduled to have talks with President
Chiluba at the State House on a wide range of issues, including
bilateral relations and the promotion of cooperation in trade,
commerce, transport and communications, a statement released by
the Ministry of Foreign Affairs said.
</P>
<P>
President Kabila is also expected to visit the Copperbelt,
which borders Zambia and Congo, in order to familiarize himself
with the area.
</P>
<P>
This is Kabila's first official visit to Zambia since his
"Alliance of Democratic Forces for the Liberation of Congo"
ousted late Mobutu Sese Seko in May this year. 
</P>
