<HEADLINE> Anshan Iron-Steel Company of China Invests in Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, September 29 (Xinhua) -- The Anshan Iron and Steel
Company, one of China's major iron and steel giants, has
established a joint venture in Cameroon as part of an ambitious
move to explore the African market.
</P>
<P>
According to sources attending the recent international trade
fair held in Anshan in northeast China's Liaoning Province, the company
will establish a small joint venture plant in Cameroon with a
local foreign trade company and African partner AUBAC.
</P>
