Total investments in the project will approach 3.15 million US
dollars, with the Chinese side holding a 55 percent share of the
venture which will have an annual production capacity of 20,000 tons.
</P>
<P>
Anshan also plans to enter the civil engineering market of
Africa and will projects such as highway and bridge construction.
</P>
<P>
Plans call for the joint venture to commence production by June
1998.  
