<HEADLINE> Chinese Official Meets Macao Senior Civil Servants </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 29 (Xinhua) -- Chen Ziying, deputy director
of the State Council Hong Kong and Macao Affairs Office, met today
with a delegation of senior civil servants from Macao.
</P>
<P>
Chen said that Macao will be a special administrative region
with a high degree of autonomy following its return to the
motherland in 1999. He said that the region will be administered
by the people of Macao in accordance with stipulations of the
Basic Law of the Macao Special Administrative Region (MSAR).
</P>
<P>
The 13-member delegation of senior civil servants will remain
in office and serve the future MSAR, Chen said, adding that he
believes the officials will contribute to the smooth transition
and social economic development of Macao.
</P>
<P>
Chen briefed the delegation on the current social and economic
situation in China's inland areas, and noted that the smooth
implementation of the "one country, two systems" principle in Hong
Kong will ensure the smooth transition and transfer of power in
Macao.
</P>
<P>
Chen expressed the hope that the visiting members will join in
concerted efforts to create an even more brilliant future for
Macao.
</P>
<P>
The delegation, which is visiting the inland area at the
invitation of the Macao Branch of Xinhua News Agency, is the third
delegation of senior civil servants from Macao to visit inland
areas. The delegation will visit inland areas and meet with
officials from the National People's Congress, the Ministry of
Personnel, the State Institute of Administration, and the Shanghai
Municipal Government.  
</P>
</TEXT>
