<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanxi To Focus on Five Pillar Industries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 29 (Xinhua) -- North China's Shanxi Province
will revamp its economic structure into five pillar industries,
according to a report in today's China Daily.
</P>
<P>
They are the coal- and coke-centered chemical system, the power
system with coal as its raw material, the metallurgical, machinery
and tourism systems, deputy governor Liu Zhenhua said recently.
</P>
<P>
Because the development of 60 key industrial groups in the
province demands astronomical investment, the provincial
government will help the enterprises raise money through various
channels, Liu said.
</P>
<P>
He said the province plans to encourage more enterprises to
issue shares at home and abroad, as well as attract more foreign
investment by improving its infrastructure and investment climate.
</P>
<P>
At present, only nine companies in the province have gone
public. This year, two or three companies in the province will
flow shares at home, Liu said.
</P>
<P>
Shanxi Province is strong in the coal, heavy chemical and
energy industries. Its annual coal production is 320 million
tons. The province provides 1.5 billion kilowatt-hours each year
to the Beijing-Tianjin-Tangshan region.
</P>
<P>
Tourism resources are also abundant in the province. About 70
percent of its ancient buildings were constructed before 600 AD,
the deputy governor said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
