<HEADLINE> Congolese President Visits Zambia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Lusaka, September 29 (Xinhua) -- President of the Democratic
Republic of Congo Laurent Kabila will arrive here today for a
three-day visit to Zambia at the invitation of his Zambian
counterpart Frederick Chilub.
</P>
<P>
Kabila will lead a high-powered delegation and is expected to hold
talks with Chiluba on a wide range of bilateral issues such as
cooperation in trade, commerce, transport and communication.
</P>
<P>
Kabila will also visit the Copperbelt province in the north
bordering Congo.
</P>
<P>
It will be the first visit to Zambia by Kabila since he took
over power in May this year after leading in an uprising to
topple former President Mobuto Sese Seko. 
</P>
</TEXT>
