<HEADLINE> Bearing Giants Bolster Business in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 29 (Xinhua) -- Two world bearing giants, SKF
Group and Timken Co, are intensifying their activities to fortify
their presence in the Chinese market, today's China Daily reported.
</P>
<P>
The Sweden-based SKF Group, one of the world's leading
rolling-bearing firms, said it had bought a 20 percent stake in
Wafangdian Bearing Ltd for 250 million yuan (30 million US
dollars).
</P>
<P>
It is negotiating with China's largest bearing producer on
another project.
</P>
<P>
SKF has invested 650 million yuan (78 million dollars) in four
joint ventures in China. Their products are used in a variety of
ways, including in textile machine tools, automobiles and
locomotives as well as bearing seals.
</P>
<P>
SKF recently established a holding company in Beijing which
oversees and coordinates operations of its joint ventures and
sales outlets in China.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the US-based Timken Co. is going to publish its
Chinese version of the Timken Tapered Roller Bearing Guide.
</P>
<P>
Nicknamed "the Bible" of the industry in the West, the book
provides complete data for 26,000 specifications in 230 kinds of
tapered roller bearings. The Chinese versions will be available in
November this year.
</P>
<P>
The step coincided with the company's rapid business growth in
China in the past two years.
</P>
<P>
The Timken Co strengthened its presence in China by setting up
a joint venture with Yantai Bearing Plant in Shandong Province in
last June. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
