<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Deng Xiaoping Theory Attracts University Students (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 29 (Xinhua) -- Yang Longbo, a senior
attending the Business School at Shanghai Teachers University, has
a notebook filled with quotations from the "Selected Works of Deng
Xiaoping", as well as a pile of newspaper clippings on Deng
Xiaoping theory.
</P>
<P>
Yang, 22, comes from a small village in a suburban Shanghai
county. The village was known as the "Village of Beggars" prior to
the 1980s.
</P>
<P>
Today, however, the villagers live in new brick homes equipped
with telephones and modern bathrooms with showers and
commodes. Many others have purchased commercial housing in
Shanghai proper, according to Yang, who believes that Deng
Xiaoping theory has brought changes to her hometown and to her own
life.
</P>
<P>
Over the past three years, Yang has received praise from the
school and various departments for the many research papers and
survey reports she has authored on the basis of Deng Xiaoping
theory.
</P>
<P>
Yang is one of many young people in over 40 colleges and
universities in Shanghai who hold high respect for Deng and are
extremely interested in studying his theory.
</P>
<P>
Students queued to purchase the third volume of the "Selected
Works of Deng Xiaoping", with the selling out within a few hours
at Shanghai Tongji University, Shanghai Teachers University and
Shanghai Medical University.
</P>
<P>
Over 4,500 students, or 94 percent of the enrollment at
Shanghai Teachers University, responded to a notice calling for
articles and essays about Deng Xiaoping theory.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
