<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Deng Xiaoping Theory Attracts University Students (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Some 1,000 students registered for a course of Deng Xiaoping
theory offered by the Polytechnic University of East China.
</P>
<P>
Han Junyi, a senior at the Shanghai Medical School, has read
some 20-odd books about Deng, including his biography, memoirs,
and theoretical works. Han expressed deep attraction for Deng's
legendary life story and great personality.
</P>
<P>
A recent survey by the State Education Commission revealed that
95 percent of the college and university students have read the
"Selected Works of Deng Xiaoping", with 91 percent students
claiming "a relatively good understanding of Deng Xiaoping
theory", and 97 percent agreeing that his theory is "highly
significant for guiding China's reform, opening and modernization
efforts."
</P>
<P>
The survey also indicated that 85 percent of students thought
that "developing and perfecting a socialist market economy is the
only way to make China strong and ensure the prosperity of the
Chinese nation", with 92 percent agreeing that the" Party's
policies on deepening reforms and speeding up development have
yielded monumental results.
</P>
<P>
Cheng Weili, a researcher with the Shanghai Academy of Social
Sciences, noted that it is quite natural that the students are
fascinated by Deng and his theory that have created unprecedented
opportunities for young people to realize their dreams. 
</P>
</TEXT>
