<HEADLINE> NZ Stocks Finish Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, September 29 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand share
market had a quiet day today, with the market indicator closing
down after opening positively in the morning.
</P>
<P>
The NZSE40 index ended 3 points lower at 2,554 with a turnover
of 44 million NZ dollars (28 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
Telecom shares led the falls, down 8 cents to 792 cents. Lion
Nathan slipped 5c to 3852c. Brierley Investment remained unchanged
for the fourth consecutive trading day at 133c.
</P>
<P>
On the rising side, Fletcher Building lifted 10c to 510c, Air
New Zealand edged up 1c to 279c, and Carter Holt Harvey gained 3c
to 342c.
</P>
<P>
However, the overall market was firmer with 67 rises against 36
falls.  
</P>
