<HEADLINE> Tanzania to Develop Cultural Tourism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, September 29 (Xinhua) -- Tanzania is making
efforts to develop and promote cultural tourism in a bid to
attract more foreign tourists to the country.
</P>
<P>
To this effect, an agreement was signed between the Tanzania
Tourist Board and the Netherlands Development Organization here
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
A joint statement issued at the signing ceremony said that
overall aim of the program is to build up a framework that can
facilitate the development and promotion of cultural forms of
tourism from which the local people can benefit in a decent way.
</P>
<P>
"Cultural tourism is one which attracts the attention of the
local people, they design and organize the tours, show tourists
several aspects of the area in which they live, and of their
daily life in a way contributing to a cultural exchange of
information," the statement noted.  
</P>
