<HEADLINE> Tanzanian Women Urged to Help Conserve </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, September 29 (Xinhua) -- Tanzanian
Vice-President Omar Ali Juma has called on women in the country
to form environmental conservation groups to fight menace of
environmental degradation, the local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
While inaugurating an environmental function in Dar es Salaam
Sunday, Juma said that participation of women is vital in
fighting the environmental degradation.
</P>
<P>
He pledged full support to the women groups where they are
formed. He urged women to set up tree nurseries which will earn
them money through selling of seedlings, hence eradicate their
poverty.
</P>
<P>
"Environment should now be a catchword to all Tanzanians, be
he a member of cultural groups, artists and even actors," Juma
stressed.
</P>
<P>
He said to food vendors, "Clean your surroundings, and wash
your utensils with hot water with the aim of conserving the
environment." 
</P>
