<HEADLINE> Denmark, Austria Help Uganda in Prison </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, September 29 (Xinhua) -- Denmark and Austria have
contributed more than 2.5 million U.S. Dollars to help Uganda
build prisons, reported ''the new vision'' daily today.
</P>
<P>
Ugandan Commissioner General of Prisons Joseph Etima was
quoted as saying that the royal danish government's contribution
of about 530,000 U.S. Dollars was already being utilized for the
rehabilitation of Masaka prison in southwestern Uganda, which was
devastated during the 1979 civil war.
</P>
<P>
He said here last week that another two million Dollars
contributed by Austria will be used for building Masindi prison
in northern Uganda.
</P>
<P>
He said the project will take off in October this year.
