<HEADLINE> Pak, Indian PMs to Meet in Edinburgh Next Month </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, September 29 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan Prime Minister
Nawaz Sharif will hold talks with his Indian counterpart I.K.
Gujral in Edinburgh, Scotland, during Commonwealth Summit meeting
scheduled for the last week of October, a local newspaper reported
today.
</P>
<P>
The two are also expected to meet in Dhaka at the invitation of
the prime minister of Bangladesh, Hasina Wajid, on the occasion of
a businessmen conference scheduled for November 19-22, The News
reported.
