<P>
East African Standard
</P>
<P>
-- The U.N. High Commissioner for Refugees in Tanzania has
rejected requests from some of the 22,000 Congolese refugees in
the border region of Kigoma to give priority to students and
civil servants in the continuing repatriation to their home
country. 
