<HEADLINE> New Objects Concerning Lord Buddha Found in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, September 29 (Xinhua) -- New archaeological objects
concerning Lord Gautam Buddha have been found in Tilaurakot and
Ramagram near Lumbini in southern Nepal, the birthplace of Lord
Buddha, local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
These objects include stone inscriptions, copper plates and
ruins of vihars (buildings) built during the period.
</P>
<P>
They were excavated by applying archaeological geophysics by
Nepal's Department of Archaeology, the United Nations Educational,
Scientific and Cultural Organization (UNESCO) and the World
Heritage Nepal, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
The archaeological objects were detected without excavating
them by earth resistance meter and magnetometer with the help of a
computer.
</P>
<P>
Representatives of the UNESCO and the World Heritage Center
were here for investigation as the government of Nepal has applied
for enlisting Ramagram and Kapilvastu under the World Heritage
list, the reports said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
