<HEADLINE> Thai Military Ready to Help Reduce Haze </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, September 29 (Xinhua) -- The Thai armed forces are
planning an operation to help ease the smoke haze brought by wind
to southern Thailand from Indonesia, press reports said today.
</P>
<P>
The operation will include making artificial rains and firing
rockets containing chemicals to eliminate the toxicity of the
smog.
</P>
<P>
Local newspapers said that Supreme Commander Gen. Mongkol
Ampronpisit has ordered the related military units to coordinate
with the Meteorological Department and the Public Health Ministry
in the operation.
</P>
<P>
The Thai navy will send its aircraft carrier HMS
Chakrinaruebet, which was purchased recently from Spain, to the
south to serve as a center for the operation.
</P>
<P>
The smoke haze produced in recent forest fires in Indonesia
began to affect eight provinces in southern Thailand last week,
with Trang province hardest hit.
</P>
<P>
The Trang airport remained closed over the weekend although
heavy rains helped reduce the haze in the south.  
</P>
</TEXT>
