<HEADLINE> Little Swan Merges With Electric Motor Supplier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, September 29 (Xinhua) -- Wuxi-based Little Swan
Co. Ltd, one of China's major washing machine producers, has
successfully merged with one of its leading suppliers of electric
motors.
</P>
<P>
The Sanjiang Electronic Appliance Manufacturing Plant, located
in northeast Jiangsu Province, has total net assets valued at 22.4
million yuan. The plant, a well-known township enterprise in
Jingjiang, is one of China's major exporters of electric motors.
</P>
<P>
Little Swan, which purchased 51 percent of Sanjiang for 50
million yuan, has transformed the new venture into a limited
liability company.
</P>
<P>
The new company will expand its current annual production
capacity of five million electric motors and will increases its
annual sales volume to some 300 million yuan, according to a
spokesman for Little Swan.
</P>
<P>
Local observers point to the fact that the merger benefits both
parties, with Sanjiang Company gaining access to greater funding
and Little Swan gaining the former's marketing strategy.
</P>
<P>
The Little Swan had earlier planned to invest 100 million yuan
to establish a plant with an annual production capacity of two
million electric motors.
</P>
<P>
Little Swan has also merged with two washing machine plants,
one each in Hubei and Liaoning provinces.
</P>
<P>
Little Swan's 1997 net profits are expected to hit 210 million
yuan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
