<HEADLINE> Collection Launched to Cater for VCD Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 29 (Xinhua) -- A total of 220 VCD programs,
comprising top foreign and domestic movies and TV series, were
launched yesterday in Beijing, according to today's China Daily.
</P>
<P>
The production of the programs aims to help satisfy China's
audio and video market, where demand is currently estimated at 100
million VCDs annually, said the Ministry of Radio, Film and
Television.
</P>
<P>
China's crackdown on pirated and pornographic VCDs and video
products over the past two years has been very successful, the
ministry said.
</P>
<P>
However, if not enough VCD products are supplied to meet the
booming market, the strenuous campaign against illegal VCD copies
will have to continue, according to the ministry.
</P>
<P>
More series of VCD programs will soon be produced jointly by
the Ministry of Radio, Film and Television, the Ministry of
Culture, the State Press and Publication Administration and the
Propaganda Department of the Communist Party of China Central
Committee.
</P>
<P>
Most of the films and TV series in the 220 VCD programs
launched yesterday are appearing on VCDs for the first
time. China-made movies and TV series outnumber overseas movies
and TV series by a ratio of 3.2.
</P>
<P>
Feature films and TV series make up 55 percent of the programs,
while 43 cartoons have also been recorded on VCD to cater for the
needs of teenagers and children.
</P>
<P>
The programs also include performances of some traditional
operas. One of the aims of the VCD collection is to raise the
popularity of traditional culture.  
</P>
</TEXT>
